  "explanation": "The defendant, a first-time offender with no prior criminal record, committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, mitigating factors are present, including the lack of criminal history and the ongoing effort to make restitution by partially paying back the funds. The disruptive outburst of a courtroom spectator has no legal bearing on the sentencing guidelines. Balancing the level of theft with the mitigating elements, a sentence of 6 months of incarceration is warranted, followed by supervised release and a requirement to pay the remaining restitution.",
